"{\"uid\": \"today.com-news-paris-olympics-olympics-opening-ceremony-last-supper-controversy-rcna163929\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"A Michael Kors Bag, Suede Slippers and More Holiday Gifts at Walmart - Starting at $9    Becca Wood  News and Trending Reporter/Editor  While thetheatrical opening ceremonyat the2024 Paris Olympicsbrought memorable moments, one scene from the performance has prompted mixed reactions.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 284, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2, \"end\": 14, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Kors\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.905945447811892e-17, \"text\": \"Michael Kors\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Kors\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michael_Kors\"}, {\"begin\": 183, \"end\": 188, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2032762773211588e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The four-hour ceremony on July 26 kicked off the start of the Summer Games, with athletes gliding down the River Seine and performers reenacting historic moments.\", \"from\": 286, \"to\": 448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 393, \"end\": 404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"River Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In one scene, drag queens and dancers lined a long table in an image that sparked controversy after some connected the moment with Leonardo da Vinci's \\\"The Last Supper\\\" portrait of Jesus Christ and his 12 apostles.\", \"from\": 450, \"to\": 664, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 581, \"end\": 598, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.2040767529432673e-39, \"text\": \"Leonardo da Vinci\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Leonardo_da_Vinci\"}, {\"begin\": 631, \"end\": 643, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.309523759247978e-14, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Though many found the moment an inclusive celebration for the LGBTQ+ community, others took to social media to call the imagery a \\\"mockery\\\" and \\\"insulting to Christian people\\\" following the performance.\", \"from\": 666, \"to\": 868, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 824, \"end\": 833, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999888316547846, \"rank\": 1.1168469527119538e-05, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On July 28, Paris 2024 spokesperson\\u00a0Anne Descamps\\u00a0apologized \\\"if people have taken any offense.\\\"\", \"from\": 870, \"to\": 966, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 882, \"end\": 892, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4871715838774485e-18, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 911, \"end\": 919, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Descamps\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jean-Baptiste_Descamps\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Clearly there was never an intention to show disrespect to any religious group.\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 1048, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On the contrary, I think that (artistic director) Thomas Jolly really tried to celebrate community tolerance,\\\" Descampssaid at a press conference.\", \"from\": 1049, \"to\": 1195, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1099, \"end\": 1105, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.965463574490792, \"rank\": 0.035769057967670805, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We believe that this ambition was achieved.\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1239, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"If people have taken any offense, we are really sorry.\\\"\", \"from\": 1240, \"to\": 1295, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"That same day, the ceremony's artistic director, Thomas Jolly,confirmed on French televisionthat da Vinci's 15th century piece was not his inspiration for the scene.\", \"from\": 1297, \"to\": 1462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1346, \"end\": 1352, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.965463574490792, \"rank\": 0.035769057967670805, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}, {\"begin\": 1372, \"end\": 1378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9984447060073379, \"rank\": 0.0013906733785231324, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Read on for why some have compared this Olympics opening ceremony performance to the \\\"The Last Supper,\\\" how people are reacting and more.\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1601, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In one scene from the opening ceremony, a dinner platter lifted to show a mainly nude French actor, Philippe Katerine, singing.\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1730, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1689, \"end\": 1695, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9984447060073379, \"rank\": 0.0013906733785231324, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1703, \"end\": 1720, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Philippe Katerine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Philippe_Katerine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the background, dancers and drag queens struck poses along a long table.\", \"from\": 1731, \"to\": 1806, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Panning through the tableau, a camera first showed a person crowned with an aureole in front of DJ turntables.\", \"from\": 1808, \"to\": 1918, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The next shot  showed the rest of the table lined with performers holding their poses.\", \"from\": 1919, \"to\": 2005, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The table then transformed into a catwalk, as the drag queens and models took the stage in homage to Paris' fashion scene.\", \"from\": 2007, \"to\": 2129, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2108, \"end\": 2113, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2032762773211588e-19, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The official X account for the Olympic Games shared photos of the moment and referenced Dionysus, Greek god of wine-making, fruitfulness and ecstasy.\", \"from\": 2131, \"to\": 2280, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2219, \"end\": 2227, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4065358751641177e-35, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}, {\"begin\": 2229, \"end\": 2234, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9999980980646693, \"rank\": 1.3847826857954527e-06, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The interpretation of the Greek God Dionysus makes us aware of the absurdity of violence between human beings,\\\"read a tweet from the official X account of the Olympics.\", \"from\": 2282, \"to\": 2451, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2309, \"end\": 2314, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9999980980646693, \"rank\": 1.3847826857954527e-06, \"text\": \"Greek\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 2319, \"end\": 2327, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4065358751641177e-35, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But some connected the tableau to the biblical scene da Vinci portrayed in \\\"The Last Supper,\\\" when Jesus Christ and his apostles shared a final meal before the crucifixion.\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2625, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2552, \"end\": 2564, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.309523759247978e-14, \"text\": \"Jesus Christ\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jesus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"When asked about the backlash July 27, the ceremony's artistic director, Thomas Jolly,said at a press conferencethat he did not intend \\\"to be subversive,\\\" \\\"mock\\\" or \\\"shock.\\\"\", \"from\": 2627, \"to\": 2800, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2700, \"end\": 2706, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"score\": 0.965463574490792, \"rank\": 0.035769057967670805, \"text\": \"Thomas\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q43115\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Thomas_the_Apostle\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We wanted to include everyone, as simple as that,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2802, \"to\": 2862, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In France, we have freedom of creation, artistic freedom.\", \"from\": 2863, \"to\": 2921, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2867, \"end\": 2873, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999883866623, \"rank\": 9.797884643922391e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We are lucky in France to live in a free country.\", \"from\": 2922, \"to\": 2971, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2938, \"end\": 2944, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999883866623, \"rank\": 9.797884643922391e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I did not have any specific messages that I wanted to deliver.\", \"from\": 2972, \"to\": 3034, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In France, we are republic, we have the right to love whom we want, we have the right not to be worshippers, we have a lot of rights in France, and this is what I wanted to convey.\\\"\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3216, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3038, \"end\": 3044, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999883866623, \"rank\": 9.797884643922391e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 3171, \"end\": 3177, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999883866623, \"rank\": 9.797884643922391e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Appearing on French news channel BFM-TV July 28, Jolly confirmed \\\"The Last Supper\\\" was not his inspiration for the piece.\", \"from\": 3218, \"to\": 3339, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3231, \"end\": 3237, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9984447060073379, \"rank\": 0.0013906733785231324, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It was not my inspiration, the Christian Last Supper,\\\" Jolly said in French.\", \"from\": 3341, \"to\": 3418, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3373, \"end\": 3382, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999888316547846, \"rank\": 1.1168469527119538e-05, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 3411, \"end\": 3417, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9984447060073379, \"rank\": 0.0013906733785231324, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is (Dionysus), who is at this table.\", \"from\": 3419, \"to\": 3462, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3430, \"end\": 3438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.4065358751641177e-35, \"text\": \"Dionysus\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Dionysius_of_Halicarnassus\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He is there because he is the god of celebration in Greek mythology, the god of wine, who is one of the jewels of France.\\\"\", \"from\": 3463, \"to\": 3585, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3515, \"end\": 3530, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"score\": 0.9999999819847291, \"rank\": 1.801540443807148e-08, \"text\": \"Greek mythology\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greek_mythology\"}, {\"begin\": 3577, \"end\": 3583, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999883866623, \"rank\": 9.797884643922391e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Jolly continued, describing the scene, \\\"And the father of Sequana, the goddess who is related to the river, the Seine.\", \"from\": 3587, \"to\": 3705, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3645, \"end\": 3652, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sequana\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sequana\"}, {\"begin\": 3699, \"end\": 3704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 7.750208544786228e-13, \"text\": \"Seine\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Seine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The idea was to have a Pagan festival linked to the Gods of Olympus.\", \"from\": 3706, \"to\": 3774, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3729, \"end\": 3734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"score\": 0.9999999998426574, \"rank\": 1.5763611957785132e-10, \"text\": \"Pagan\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paganism\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"You will never find in me a desire to mock and denigrate anyone.\\\"\", \"from\": 3775, \"to\": 3840, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some were supportive of the artistic vision, arguing the tableau was fighting to make a statement on inclusivity.\", \"from\": 3842, \"to\": 3955, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We know in the LGBTQ community in France we are far from what the ceremony showed.\", \"from\": 3957, \"to\": 4040, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3992, \"end\": 3998, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999883866623, \"rank\": 9.797884643922391e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"There is much progress to do in society regarding transgender people.\", \"from\": 4041, \"to\": 4110, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's terrible that to legally change their identity they are forced to be on trial,\\\" France's Inter-LGBT President James Leperlier said, perthe AP.\", \"from\": 4111, \"to\": 4258, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4196, \"end\": 4202, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999883866623, \"rank\": 9.797884643922391e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 4205, \"end\": 4215, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inter-LGBT\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Inter-LGBT\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inter-LGBT\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Inter-LGBT\"}, {\"begin\": 4226, \"end\": 4231, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Epistle_of_James\", \"score\": 0.9970775402675889, \"rank\": 0.0028260580591295144, \"text\": \"James\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Epistle_of_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Epistle_of_James\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Speaking to French newspaper Le Parisien, Katerine said in French that the entire ceremony was \\\"moving\\\" and \\\"grandiose.\\\"\", \"from\": 4260, \"to\": 4380, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4272, \"end\": 4278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9984447060073379, \"rank\": 0.0013906733785231324, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 4289, \"end\": 4300, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Parisien\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Le Parisien\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q11032\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Parisien\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Le_Parisien\"}, {\"begin\": 4319, \"end\": 4325, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.9984447060073379, \"rank\": 0.0013906733785231324, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I was proud of it because it's my culture.\", \"from\": 4382, \"to\": 4425, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"We are full of different people and each person lives in their own way and above all has the right to do so.\", \"from\": 4426, \"to\": 4534, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I loved doing it,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 4535, \"to\": 4562, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Katerine added that he hoped to get the following message across: \\\"If we are naked, there is no war because there are no weapons.\\\"\", \"from\": 4564, \"to\": 4694, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Drag Race France\\\" hostNicky Doll, one of the performers, told TODAY.comthat any negativity following the performance \\\"has not really affected me.\\\"\", \"from\": 4696, \"to\": 4843, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"First and foremost, it was definitely an honor.\", \"from\": 4845, \"to\": 4893, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"France took very seriously the role of being the host of these Olympics, and we really wanted to showcase the depth of French culture,\\\" Nicky said.\", \"from\": 4894, \"to\": 5041, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4894, \"end\": 4900, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999883866623, \"rank\": 9.797884643922391e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 5013, \"end\": 5027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French culture\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Culture_of_France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She continued, \\\"It was not just about queer people or drag, it was also about waacking, about the ballroom scene, about vogueing, about hip hop.\", \"from\": 5043, \"to\": 5187, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was all about music and celebration and a big banquet and a big party.\\\"\", \"from\": 5188, \"to\": 5262, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Le Filip, who won the third season of \\\"Drag Race France\\\" this year, told AP they were \\\"amazed.\\\"\", \"from\": 5264, \"to\": 5359, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5337, \"end\": 5339, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.0592751660995894e-16, \"text\": \"AP\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Associated_Press\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I thought it would be a five-minute drag event with queer representation.\", \"from\": 5361, \"to\": 5435, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was amazed.\", \"from\": 5436, \"to\": 5449, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It started with Lady Gaga, then we had drag queens, a huge rave, and a fire in the sky.\", \"from\": 5450, \"to\": 5537, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5466, \"end\": 5475, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Lady Gaga\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lady_Gaga\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It felt like a crowning all over again.\", \"from\": 5538, \"to\": 5577, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I am proud to see my friends and queer people on the world stage,\\\" Le Filip said.\", \"from\": 5578, \"to\": 5659, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Others, including celebrities, U.S. political figures and Catholic church leaders, expressed outrage at the scene.\", \"from\": 5661, \"to\": 5775, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5692, \"end\": 5696, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9999997924014894, \"rank\": 1.217465851396801e-07, \"text\": \"U.S.\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}, {\"begin\": 5719, \"end\": 5727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 1.5889292872666955e-12, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Vatican issued a statement Aug. 3, writing, \\\"The Holy See was saddened by certain scenes at the opening ceremony of the Paris Olympic Games and can only join the voices raised in recent days to deplore the offence caused to many Christians and believers of other religions.\\\"\", \"from\": 5777, \"to\": 6055, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6010, \"end\": 6020, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"score\": 0.5786925159962163, \"rank\": 0.7279156797266199, \"text\": \"Christians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/History_of_Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Roman Catholic Church center added that at such a \\\"prestigious event\\\" as the Olympics, \\\"there should not be allusions that ridicule the religious convictions of many people.\\\"\", \"from\": 6057, \"to\": 6235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6061, \"end\": 6082, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.9548855100018456e-13, \"text\": \"Roman Catholic Church\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Freedom of expression, which of course is not in question, finds its limit in respect for others,\\\" the statement read.\", \"from\": 6237, \"to\": 6356, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Actor Candace Cameron Bure, whose husband is a two-time Olympic medalist,called the performance \\\"disgusting.\\\"\", \"from\": 6358, \"to\": 6467, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6364, \"end\": 6384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Cameron_Bure\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Candace Cameron Bure\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Cameron_Bure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Candace_Cameron_Bure\"}, {\"begin\": 6380, \"end\": 6384, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"score\": 0.9821958684230754, \"rank\": 0.018126864660133857, \"text\": \"Bure\", \"types\": [\"Q47521\", \"Q4022\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/River_Bure\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"(To) see the opening ceremonies completely blaspheme and mock the Christian faith with their interpretation of the Last Supper was disgusting,\\\" she said inan Instagram post July 28.\", \"from\": 6469, \"to\": 6651, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6536, \"end\": 6545, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.9999888316547846, \"rank\": 1.1168469527119538e-05, \"text\": \"Christian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It made me so sad.\", \"from\": 6652, \"to\": 6671, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And someone said, 'You should not be sad.\", \"from\": 6672, \"to\": 6713, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You should be mad about it.'\", \"from\": 6714, \"to\": 6742, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And I am like, 'Trust me.\", \"from\": 6743, \"to\": 6768, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It makes me mad.'\", \"from\": 6769, \"to\": 6786, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I am more sad, because I am sad for souls.\\\"\", \"from\": 6787, \"to\": 6834, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"House Speaker Mike Johnsonshared an image July 27of the scene on X and called the tableau \\\"shocking\\\" and \\\"insulting.\\\"\", \"from\": 6836, \"to\": 6953, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6836, \"end\": 6849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.5623051537614153e-14, \"text\": \"House Speaker\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Speaker_of_the_United_States_House_of_Representatives\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Catholic leaders in France called the scene a \\\"mockery of Christianity\\\" in a statement,Reuters reported.\", \"from\": 6955, \"to\": 7059, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6955, \"end\": 6963, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"score\": 0.9999999999972715, \"rank\": 1.5889292872666955e-12, \"text\": \"Catholic\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catholic_Church\"}, {\"begin\": 6975, \"end\": 6981, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999883866623, \"rank\": 9.797884643922391e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 7013, \"end\": 7025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.8687993329287782, \"rank\": 0.15101377510113487, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}, {\"begin\": 7042, \"end\": 7049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.607315992546994e-22, \"text\": \"Reuters\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Reuters\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This ceremony has unfortunately included scenes of derision and mockery of Christianity, which we very deeply deplore,\\\" the Conference of French bishops said in a statement.\", \"from\": 7061, \"to\": 7235, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7137, \"end\": 7149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"score\": 0.8687993329287782, \"rank\": 0.15101377510113487, \"text\": \"Christianity\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Christianity\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Harrison Butker, the Kansas City Chiefs kicker who gave a controversial commencementspeechtouching on\\u00a0birth control, COVID-19 restrictions, women's roles and moreearlier this year, quoted the Bible onXafter the ceremony.\", \"from\": 7237, \"to\": 7457, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7237, \"end\": 7252, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrison_Butker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Harrison Butker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q14128148\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrison_Butker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Harrison_Butker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"'Be not deceived, God is not mocked.\", \"from\": 7459, \"to\": 7496, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For what things a man shall sow, those also shall he reap.\", \"from\": 7497, \"to\": 7555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For he that soweth in his flesh, of the flesh also shall reap corruption.\", \"from\": 7556, \"to\": 7629, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But he that soweth in the spirit, of the spirit shall reap life everlasting,'\\\" he wrote, citing, \\\"Galatians 6:7-8.\\\"\", \"from\": 7630, \"to\": 7745, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7728, \"end\": 7737, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Epistle_to_the_Galatians\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.623617824415727e-31, \"text\": \"Galatians\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Epistle_to_the_Galatians\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Epistle_to_the_Galatians\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Peacock is streaming the Paris Olympics around the clock.Learn more about accounts here.\", \"from\": 7747, \"to\": 7835, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"TODAY earns a commission on purchases.\", \"from\": 7836, \"to\": 7874, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Peacock is owned by our parent company NBCUniversal.\", \"from\": 7875, \"to\": 7927, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7914, \"end\": 7926, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9863448279246853e-13, \"text\": \"NBCUniversal\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NBCUniversal\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Becca Wood is a news and trending reporter for TODAY Digital based in New York City.\", \"from\": 7929, \"to\": 8013, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7999, \"end\": 8012, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.535195149185457e-14, \"text\": \"New York City\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/New_York_City\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Follow her on Instagram and Twitter.\", \"from\": 8014, \"to\": 8050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8028, \"end\": 8037, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1283240184264976e-46, \"text\": \"Instagram\", \"types\": [\"Q7397\", \"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Instagram\"}, {\"begin\": 8042, \"end\": 8049, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.3058269819550477e-33, \"text\": \"Twitter\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Twitter\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\u00a9\\u00a02025 NBCUniversal Media, LLCApple\\u00ae, Apple logo\\u00ae and App Store\\u00ae are registered trademarks of Apple Inc.\", \"from\": 8052, \"to\": 8156, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 8090, \"end\": 8095, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8237538137980883e-13, \"text\": \"Apple\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}, {\"begin\": 8106, \"end\": 8115, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/App_store\", \"score\": 0.99999692024377, \"rank\": 3.0797656527961454e-06, \"text\": \"App Store\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/App_store\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/App_store\"}, {\"begin\": 8146, \"end\": 8156, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.903480321382241e-41, \"text\": \"Apple Inc.\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Apple_Inc.\"}]}]}"